  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN167-kilavi">talaimakaṉ poruḷkaṭaikkūṭṭiya neñciṟkuc collic celavaḻuṅkiyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">How he prevented going by speaking to the heart that coveted wealth.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="AN167">
        <l><anchor n="1"/>vayaṅkumaṇi poruta vakaiyamai vaṉappiṟ</l>
        <l>pacuṅkā ḻa<supplied>l</supplied>kuṉ māa yōḷoṭu</l>
        <l>viṉaivaṉap peytiya puṉaipūñ cēkkai</l>
        <l>viṇporu neṭunakart taṅki yiṉṟē</l>
        <l>yi<supplied>ṉi</supplied>tuṭaṉ kaḻintaṉṟu maṉṉē nāḷaip</l>
        <l>poruntāk kaṇṇem pulampuvan tuṟutarac</l>
        <l>cēkkuvaṅ kollō neñcē cātteṟin</l>
        <l>tatarkūṭ ṭuṇṇu maṇaṅkuṭaip pakaḻik</l>
        <l>koṭuvi lāṭavar <supplied>pa</supplied>ṭupakai ve<supplied>rī</supplied>i</l>
        <l>yūreḻun tulaṟiya pīreḻu mutupāḻ</l>
        <l>muruṅkai mēynta peruṅkai yāṉai</l>
        <l>veri<supplied>nō</supplied>ṅku ciṟupuṟa muriñca volki</l>
        <l>yiṭṭikai neṭuñcuvar viṭṭam vīḻnteṉa</l>
        <l>maṇippu<supplied>ṟā</supplied>t tuṟanta marañcōr māṭat</l>
        <l>teḻutaṇi kaṭavuḷ pōkaliṟ pulleṉ</l>
        <l>ṟoḻukupali maṟanta meḻukāp puṉṟiṇaip</l>
        <l>pāṉāy tuḷḷiya paṟaikkaṭ cīṟiṟ</l>
        <l>kuyilkā<supplied>ḻ</supplied> citaiya maṇṭi yayilvāyk</l>
        <l>kūrmukac citalai vēynta</l>
        <l>pōrmaṭi nalliṟaip potiyi lāṉē.</l> 
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>Staying in the tall mansion that touches the sky, (4a-c)</l>
        <l>on the bed with flowers as a decoration that attained beauty by craftsmanship, (3)</l>
        <l>with the dark one, a green pearl-string on [her] hips, (2)</l>
        <l>[her] beauty close to the kind that contests glowing gems</l>
        <l>today has passed sweetly, [being] together. Tomorrow, (4d-5)</l>
        <l>shall we dwell, o heart, (7a-c)</l>
        <l>with eyes that are not content, while loneliness comes [and] is suffered, (6)</l>
        <l>frightened by the enmity coming from men with cruel/curved bows (9)</l>
        <l>[and] dreadful arrows, who jointly eat on the road after attacking a caravan, (7d-8)</l>
        <l>in the old waste land where sponge gourds rise that are dried up after growing in the village,</l>
        <l>– in the public hall with good eaves that fold under the war, (20)</l>
        <l>covered with termites, [their] sharp faces (19)</l>
        <l>with lance[-like] mouths, devastatingly boring into the perforated rafters (18)</l>
        <l>of the little house with a worn spot on which dogs jumped about for milk, (17)</l>
        <l>with an uncleansed empty veranda, that has forgotten the offerings that flew (16)</l>
        <l>in vain, because the god adorned by drawing had gone (15)</l>
        <l>from the storied mansion, languishing with [its] tree that was abandoned by the ring dove, (14)</l>
        <l>because a cross beam fell from a long brick wall, (13)</l>
        <l>weakened when the large-trunked elephant that grazed on horseradish</l>
        <l>rubbed the nape high on [its] back [against it], (11f.)</l>
        <l>in the old waste land where sponge gourd grows that had withered after growing in the village? (10)</l>
      </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>

